To celebrate International Day of the Girl, First Lady Jill Biden is honoring 15 young women who are making a difference in their communities. These women are being recognized for their leadership and efforts in areas such as ending period poverty, advocating for gun violence prevention, combating online harassment, fighting against book bans, combating antisemitism, advocating for disability rights, addressing climate change, promoting civic engagement, promoting food security and sustainability, supporting refugee resettlement, advancing STEM education, supporting military teens, promoting civic education, and ending "book deserts" for disadvantaged preschool children. The Biden-Harris Administration is also announcing new actions to expand opportunities for women and girls. The celebration, called "Girls Leading Change," will be livestreamed from the White House.